ous omnipresence and invisibility, effectively breaking down the barriers of sexual identity. Hetero offers a collective call to expand the ways in which queer theory is applied and put into practical use, and exposes the queer nature of the love that does dare speak its name.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aCultural Studies : Popular Culture. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh1 aBenshoff, Harry M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCampbell, Allan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeAngelis, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerstner, David A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriffin, Sean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGriffin, Sean, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHaralovich, Mary Beth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeffernan, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLugowski, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcLean, Adrienne L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNegra, Diane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSarkar, Bhaskar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSturtevant, Victoria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWallenberg, Louise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org